# Enler — Flutter Coding Standards

## Widget Structure

### File Template
Every screen/widget file should follow this order:
```dart
// 1. Dart/Flutter imports
// 2. Package imports
// 3. Project imports (relative within feature, package for cross-feature)
// 4. Part directives (for Freezed/Riverpod code-gen)

class MyWidget extends ConsumerWidget {
  const MyWidget({super.key}); // Always const constructor

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final theme = Theme.of(context);       // Access theme
    final l10n = AppLocalizations.of(context)!; // Access localization

    return ...; // Widget tree
  }
}
```

### Rules
- Always use `const` constructors when possible.
- Prefer `ConsumerWidget` / `ConsumerStatefulWidget` over `Consumer` wrapper.
- Extract sub-widgets into separate classes when they exceed ~50 lines.
- No God-widgets — if `build()` exceeds 100 lines, split it.
- Use `Key` wisely — provide keys for list items and animated widgets.
- Never use `MediaQuery.of(context)` directly for sizing — use `LayoutBuilder` or `MediaQuery.sizeOf(context)` (Flutter 3.10+).

### Widget Decomposition Pattern
```
feature_screen.dart          # Screen (scaffold, appbar, layout)
├── _feature_body.dart       # Body content (private widget or same file)
├── feature_card.dart         # Reusable card component
└── feature_empty_state.dart  # Empty state widget
```

## State Management — Riverpod

### Provider Organization
- One file per provider (or closely related group).
- Providers live in `presentation/providers/` within each feature.
- Shared providers go in `shared/providers/`.
- Name providers descriptively: `quizSessionProvider`, `userProfileProvider`.

### Code-Gen (Preferred)
```dart
@riverpod
class QuizSession extends _$QuizSession {
  @override
  FutureOr<QuizState> build(String quizId) async {
    return await ref.read(quizRepositoryProvider).getSession(quizId);
  }

  Future<void> submitAnswer(String answerId) async {
    state = const AsyncValue.loading();
    state = await AsyncValue.guard(() async {
      return ref.read(quizRepositoryProvider).submitAnswer(answerId);
    });
  }
}
```

### Rules
- Always handle `AsyncValue` states: `when(data:, loading:, error:)`.
- Use `ref.watch()` in build methods, `ref.read()` in callbacks/event handlers.
- Never call `ref.watch()` inside conditionals or loops.
- Auto-dispose is default with code-gen — keep it unless you have a good reason.
- For one-time actions (navigation, snackbar), use `ref.listen()`.

### Dependency Injection
```dart
// Repository provider (auto-generated from @riverpod)
@riverpod
AuthRepository authRepository(AuthRepositoryRef ref) {
  return AuthRepository(supabase: ref.read(supabaseClientProvider));
}
```

## Theming — Soft Aurora

### Accessing Colors
```dart
// ✅ Correct
final primary = Theme.of(context).colorScheme.primary;
final bgColor = Theme.of(context).colorScheme.surface;

// ❌ Wrong — never hardcode colors
final primary = Color(0xFF6366F1);
```

### Accessing Text Styles
```dart
// ✅ Correct
Text('Hello', style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.headlineMedium);

// ❌ Wrong — never create ad-hoc styles
Text('Hello', style: TextStyle(fontSize: 24, fontWeight: FontWeight.bold));
```

### Custom Tokens (for tokens not in Material 3)
Access via theme extensions:
```dart
final enlerColors = Theme.of(context).extension<EnlerColors>()!;
final warmAccent = enlerColors.warmAccent;    // #F472B6
final rewardColor = enlerColors.reward;        // #F59E0B
```

### Gradients
```dart
// Share card gradient — always use the constant
const kShareCardGradient = LinearGradient(
  colors: [Color(0xFF6366F1), Color(0xFF8B5CF6)],
  begin: Alignment.topLeft,
  end: Alignment.bottomRight,
);
```

## Localization

### Access Pattern
```dart
// Define a short alias in core/extensions/
extension BuildContextL10n on BuildContext {
  AppLocalizations get l10n => AppLocalizations.of(this)!;
}

// Usage
Text(context.l10n.profileTitle); // "Profilim"
```

### Rules
- Every user-visible string must be in `app_tr.arb`.
- Use ICU message format for plurals and parameters:
  ```json
  "quizScore": "{score} puan kazandın!",
  "friendCount": "{count, plural, =0{Henüz arkadaş yok} =1{1 arkadaş} other{{count} arkadaş}}"
  ```
- Never concatenate strings — use parameterized messages.

## Supabase Client Usage

### Query Pattern
```dart
// ✅ Correct — specific columns, error handling
final response = await supabase
    .from('profiles')
    .select('id, username, avatar_url')
    .eq('id', userId)
    .maybeSingle();

// ❌ Wrong — select all columns
final response = await supabase.from('profiles').select('*');

// ❌ Wrong — single() throws on no result
final response = await supabase.from('profiles').select().single();
```

### Realtime
```dart
// Use StreamProvider for Realtime subscriptions
@riverpod
Stream<List<QuizAnswer>> quizAnswers(QuizAnswersRef ref, String sessionId) {
  return supabase
      .from('quiz_answers')
      .stream(primaryKey: ['id'])
      .eq('session_id', sessionId)
      .map((rows) => rows.map(QuizAnswer.fromJson).toList());
}
```

## Navigation — GoRouter

### Route Definition
```dart
GoRoute(
  path: '/quiz/:id',
  name: 'quiz',
  builder: (context, state) {
    final quizId = state.pathParameters['id']!;
    return QuizScreen(quizId: quizId);
  },
),
```

### Navigation
```dart
// ✅ Named routes
context.goNamed('quiz', pathParameters: {'id': quizId});

// ✅ Push for stack navigation
context.pushNamed('quiz', pathParameters: {'id': quizId});

// ❌ Never use Navigator.push directly
Navigator.push(context, MaterialPageRoute(...));
```

## Model Layer — Freezed

### Pattern
```dart
@freezed
class UserProfile with _$UserProfile {
  const factory UserProfile({
    required String id,
    required String username,
    String? avatarUrl,
    @Default(0) int quizCount,
  }) = _UserProfile;

  factory UserProfile.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) =>
      _$UserProfileFromJson(json);
}
```

### Rules
- All domain models use Freezed.
- DTOs (Data Transfer Objects) can be plain classes if Freezed is overkill.
- Use `@Default()` for optional fields with defaults.
- Use union types for state modeling:
  ```dart
  @freezed
  sealed class QuizState with _$QuizState {
    const factory QuizState.initial() = QuizInitial;
    const factory QuizState.playing({required Question question}) = QuizPlaying;
    const factory QuizState.finished({required int score}) = QuizFinished;
  }
  ```

## Performance

### Critical Rules
- ✅ `const` constructors everywhere.
- ✅ `ListView.builder` for any list with 10+ items.
- ✅ `RepaintBoundary` around expensive subtrees (animations, complex layouts).
- ✅ `cached_network_image` for all network images.
- ✅ Image assets at proper resolution (1x, 2x, 3x).
- ❌ No `BackdropFilter` on main scrollable content — kills mid-range Android perf.
- ❌ No `Opacity` widget for fading — use `AnimatedOpacity` or `FadeTransition`.
- ❌ No unnecessary `setState` — prefer Riverpod state updates.
- ❌ No `print()` statements — use `debugPrint()` or a logging package.

### Image Guidelines
```dart
// ✅ Use cached_network_image
CachedNetworkImage(
  imageUrl: avatarUrl,
  width: 48,
  height: 48,
  fit: BoxFit.cover,
  placeholder: (_, __) => const AvatarPlaceholder(),
  errorWidget: (_, __, ___) => const AvatarFallback(),
)
```

## Testing

### Unit Tests (Domain + Data)
```dart
// test/features/quiz/domain/quiz_service_test.dart
void main() {
  group('QuizService', () {
    late QuizService service;
    late MockQuizRepository mockRepo;

    setUp(() {
      mockRepo = MockQuizRepository();
      service = QuizService(repository: mockRepo);
    });

    test('calculateScore returns correct percentage', () {
      expect(service.calculateScore(correct: 7, total: 10), 70);
    });
  });
}
```

### Widget Tests
```dart
void main() {
  testWidgets('QuizCard displays question text', (tester) async {
    await tester.pumpWidget(
      const ProviderScope(
        child: MaterialApp(
          home: QuizCard(question: 'Favorite movie?'),
        ),
      ),
    );

    expect(find.text('Favorite movie?'), findsOneWidget);
  });
}
```

### Rules
- Test files live alongside source files: `quiz_service_test.dart` next to `quiz_service.dart`, or in a mirrored `test/` directory.
- Mock repositories with `mockito` or `mocktail` — generated mocks preferred.
- Wrap widgets in `ProviderScope` for tests using Riverpod.
- Test error states, not just happy paths.
- Minimum coverage: all domain logic and repository methods.

## Error Handling

### Pattern
```dart
// Use AsyncValue.guard for async operations
state = await AsyncValue.guard(() async {
  return await repository.fetchData();
});

// Display errors consistently
ref.watch(someProvider).when(
  data: (data) => DataWidget(data: data),
  loading: () => const EnlerLoadingIndicator(),
  error: (error, stack) => EnlerErrorWidget(
    message: context.l10n.genericError,
    onRetry: () => ref.invalidate(someProvider),
  ),
);
```

### Rules
- Never silently swallow exceptions — log them at minimum.
- Show user-friendly error messages from localization, not raw exception text.
- Always provide a retry mechanism for network errors.
- Use custom exception classes for domain-specific errors.

